# Astro architecture

## Stack defaults

- Prefer static Astro HTML/CSS. Do not add React/Vue/Svelte or `client:*` islands unless interaction cannot be done with light vanilla JS.
- Progressive enhancement lives in `@src/scripts/main.js`, not framework islands.
- Package manager is `pnpm`; Node `>=22.12`. Deploy via existing Wrangler/Cloudflare config when touching deploy.

## Structure

- Pages compose section components (see `@src/pages/index.astro`).
- Shared chrome and document head via `@src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro`.
- Site copy, contact info, services, reviews, and SEO defaults live in `@src/data/site.ts` — do not scatter the same strings across components.
- Design tokens (colors, fonts) live in `@src/styles/global.css` under `@theme` (Tailwind v4). Use those utilities (`bg-page`, `text-accent`, `font-display`) instead of inventing new hex values.

## Do / don't

```astro
<!-- ❌ BAD: framework island for a simple menu -->
<MobileNav client:load />

<!-- ✅ GOOD: static markup + small script in main.js -->
<button id="nav-burger" aria-expanded="false">…</button>
```

```ts
// ❌ BAD: hardcode business email in three components
// ✅ GOOD: import { site } from '../data/site'
```
